article.description: Taylor Rohde scored 28 points -- 16 from the free-throw line -- and added 12 rebounds as Alaska-Anchorage defeated UC Irvine 77-63 in the seventh-place game of the Great Alaska Shootout.
article.headline: UC Irvine still winless as Alaska-Anchorage wins
article.linkText: UC Irvine still winless as Alaska-Anchorage wins
article.story: ANCHORAGE, Alaska -- Taylor Rohde scored 28 points -- 16 from the free-throw line -- and added 12 rebounds as Alaska-Anchorage defeated UC Irvine 77-63 in the seventh-place game of the Great Alaska Shootout. Travis Thompson and Abebe Demissie had 13 points apiece for the Division II Seawolves (1-2) and Lonnie Ridgway scored 11 points. Rohde was 16 for 18 from the foul line while UC Irvine went 10 for 16 as a team. The Anteaters (0-6) scored the game's first seven points, but the host Seawolves took their first lead at 29-28. UC Irvine led 44-42 at halftime but managed just 19 points in the second half, and was outscored 13-2 in the final 7 1/2 minutes. Daman Starring had 21 points to lead UC Irvine.
